{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"06126151-8793-4d4c-a1a2-15ecd0ba2d1c","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's a general guide for the switch:\n\n### Changes needed for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. NuGet.org setup:**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions policy: specify your **repo owner**, **repo name**, **branch/tag**, and optionally the **workflow file** and **environment**\n\n**2. Workflow changes:**\n\nAdd `id-token: write` permission and replace the API key push:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      contents: read\n      id-token: write          # ← Required for OIDC\n    # Optional but recommended: tie to a GitHub environment\n    # environment: nuget-publish\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.0.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # Replace:\n      #   dotnet nuget push ... --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n      # With:\n      - name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n        run: |\n          dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n            --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**3. Key differences:**\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | No secret needed |\n| `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | No `--api-key` flag |\n| No `permissions` block needed | `id-token: write` required |\n\n**4. Cleanup:**\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` repository secret once verified\n- Consider revoking the old API key on nuget.org\n\n> **Note:** NuGet trusted publishing is still relatively new. Verify your `dotnet` SDK version supports it (6.0.4xx+ / 7.0+). The NuGet server authenticates your workflow via the OIDC token automatically — no API key is exchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af6354f1-adc8-4868-adce-e20c61638480","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":602,"requestId":"6C46:23A25:D241B9:1068A2F:6A012A30"},"id":"4ed18e43-7eec-4865-960f-b66d5bffe823","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:00:45.795Z","parentId":"f8029a04-cff3-428a-93b5-52b11a259e75"}
